From: Ray Liu <ray.xy.liu@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 8 May 2026 10:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] pinctrl: airoha: allow build on ARMv7 AArch32 (AN7563)

The Airoha AN7563 / AN7552 SoC reuses the EN7581 chip-SCU and SCU
register layouts, including the IOMUX / PHY-LED / GPIO blocks driven
by drivers/pinctrl/mediatek/pinctrl-airoha.c, but boots its
Cortex-A53 cluster in 32-bit AArch32 mode. With the original
"depends on ARM64 || COMPILE_TEST" the driver cannot be built on the
AN7563 ARMv7 kernel, even though the underlying register layout is
identical.

Relax the architecture dependency to also accept ARM, so that ARMv7
configurations targeting AN7563 (or any future EN7581-derivative
that still boots in AArch32 mode) can build pinctrl-airoha
unmodified.

Signed-off-by: Ray Liu <ray.xy.liu@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/pinctrl/mediatek/Kconfig | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/pinctrl/mediatek/Kconfig
+++ b/drivers/pinctrl/mediatek/Kconfig
@@ -129,7 +129,7 @@ config PINCTRL_MT8127
 config PINCTRL_AIROHA
 	tristate "Airoha EN7581 pin control"
 	depends on OF
-	depends on ARM64 || COMPILE_TEST
+	depends on ARM || ARM64 || COMPILE_TEST
 	select PINMUX
 	select GENERIC_PINCONF
 	select GENERIC_PINCTRL_GROUPS
